1
00:00:04,491 --> 00:00:06,792
The Chairman is here.

2
00:00:08,010 --> 00:00:14,960


3
00:00:19,771 --> 00:00:21,242
Welcome.

4
00:00:21,242 --> 00:00:23,812
Congratulations, Sir.

5
00:00:23,812 --> 00:00:27,622
- Congratulations. 
 - Congratulations.

6
00:00:28,952 --> 00:00:30,321
Congratulations.

7
00:00:30,321 --> 00:00:33,652
- Congratulations. 
 - Hello.

8
00:00:33,652 --> 00:00:36,141
 Congratulations, Sir. 

9
00:00:57,382 --> 00:01:00,751
 The founder of Soonyang. 

10
00:01:01,551 --> 00:01:05,051
 It's him. Chairman Jin Yang Cheol. 

11
00:01:06,391 --> 00:01:10,092
 This is a dream. It can't be reality. 

12
00:01:12,932 --> 00:01:15,661
 He died twenty years ago. 

13
00:01:22,072 --> 00:01:24,071
 How could this be? 

14
00:01:38,452 --> 00:01:40,191
Do Jun.

15
00:01:41,121 --> 00:01:43,261
Forgive me, Father.

16
00:01:56,741 --> 00:02:01,381
Do Jun, you should watch your manners when you're around Grandfather.

17
00:02:01,381 --> 00:02:05,151
He's young. It happens when you're overwhelmed.

18
00:02:05,151 --> 00:02:08,621
I'll watch Do Jun. You can go on ahead.

19
00:02:08,621 --> 00:02:10,192
Okay, then.

20
00:02:10,192 --> 00:02:12,491
You sweet boy.

21
00:02:15,591 --> 00:02:18,491
That's what your grandfather is like.

22
00:02:18,491 --> 00:02:21,562
Nothing about his life is fun.

23
00:02:21,562 --> 00:02:24,572
Would thorns break out of his hand

24
00:02:24,572 --> 00:02:27,942
if he were to just stroke your head?

25
00:02:27,942 --> 00:02:32,711
Do Jun, come with Grandma.

26
00:02:32,711 --> 00:02:36,611
- "Grandma"? 
 - Yes, Sweetie.

27
00:02:39,111 --> 00:02:40,781
Who...

28
00:02:41,521 --> 00:02:43,782
Who am I?

29
00:02:43,782 --> 00:02:45,122
You're so silly.

30
00:02:45,122 --> 00:02:49,262
What do you mean, who are you? You are Jin Do Jun,

31
00:02:49,262 --> 00:02:52,212
the youngest grandchild of the Soonyang family.

32
00:03:00,372 --> 00:03:02,922
   

33
00:03:04,141 --> 00:03:09,041
Is it the year 1987?

34
00:03:10,352 --> 00:03:15,152
Am I a member of Chairman Jin Yang Cheol's family?

35
00:03:15,152 --> 00:03:17,382
The youngest?

36
00:03:17,382 --> 00:03:19,291
This can't be.

37
00:03:21,062 --> 00:03:23,121
   

38
00:03:23,121 --> 00:03:27,401
   

39
00:03:27,401 --> 00:03:29,932
   

40
00:03:32,901 --> 00:03:36,542
Hyeong Jun, Do Jun, it's your first visit, isn't it?

41
00:03:37,872 --> 00:03:39,641
This is Grandpa's place.

42
00:03:39,641 --> 00:03:42,742
Whoa. Is this the main entrance?

43
00:03:42,742 --> 00:03:44,052
It's massive.

44
00:03:44,052 --> 00:03:46,112
 It's just the same. 

45
00:03:46,112 --> 00:03:50,981
 Jeongsimjae, the Soonyang residence that had been theirs for generations. 

46
00:03:51,692 --> 00:03:53,662
 A monk well-versed in geomancy 

47
00:03:53,662 --> 00:03:57,892
 picked out the auspicious spot for a home and told Chairman Jin 

48
00:03:57,892 --> 00:04:02,762
  that as long as they were good at heart, their money would never dry up. 

49
00:04:03,432 --> 00:04:05,932
 The name "Jeongsimjae..." 

50
00:04:05,932 --> 00:04:08,901
 literally means "righteous heart." 

51
00:04:27,562 --> 00:04:30,492
Wow, this is amazing.

52
00:04:32,132 --> 00:04:35,202
One, two, three, four, five.

53
00:04:35,202 --> 00:04:37,932
Gosh. How many rooms are there?

54
00:04:37,932 --> 00:04:39,772
Thirteen.

55
00:04:40,672 --> 00:04:43,512
What? How do you know that?

56
00:04:43,512 --> 00:04:46,642
Have you been here without me?

57
00:04:46,642 --> 00:04:49,012
Don't be silly.

58
00:04:49,012 --> 00:04:51,512
Hyeong Jun, you promised Mom.

59
00:04:51,512 --> 00:04:53,521
That you'll be a good boy today.

60
00:04:53,521 --> 00:04:55,021
Yes.

61
00:04:56,052 --> 00:04:57,952
Do Jun, you too.

62
00:04:58,791 --> 00:05:00,322
Don't get too nervous.

63
00:05:00,322 --> 00:05:03,962
I think you're the one who’s nervous.

64
00:05:03,962 --> 00:05:05,431
What?

65
00:05:06,762 --> 00:05:11,271
Let's go. Grandma and Grandpa will be waiting.

66
00:05:12,502 --> 00:05:14,041
Come along.

67
00:05:24,851 --> 00:05:29,122
♪  Bells toll and flowers are in bloom   ♪

68
00:05:29,122 --> 00:05:33,351
♪   Birds sing and people smile  ♪

69
00:05:33,351 --> 00:05:37,692
♪   I miss you, my love  ♪

70
00:05:37,692 --> 00:05:41,261
♪   Please do not leave my side  ♪

71
00:05:41,261 --> 00:05:45,672
♪   Where we first met and fell in love  ♪

72
00:05:45,672 --> 00:05:49,971
♪   The sweet roads I gave my heart to  ♪

73
00:05:49,971 --> 00:05:54,081
♪   In beautiful Seoul  ♪

74
00:05:54,081 --> 00:05:59,152
♪   I want to live in Seoul  ♪

75
00:06:14,562 --> 00:06:17,971
However busy you are, the meat and fish cannot be cold.

76
00:06:17,971 --> 00:06:21,971
Reheat and re-serve every now and then.

77
00:06:26,512 --> 00:06:29,211
- Do not scrimp on the salt. 
 - I understand.

78
00:06:29,211 --> 00:06:32,212
People these days eat less salt to stay healthy,

79
00:06:32,212 --> 00:06:34,181
but food must be seasoned enough.

80
00:06:34,181 --> 00:06:36,751
Don't worry about that, Mother.

81
00:06:36,751 --> 00:06:39,692
Your first daughter-in-law has everything under control.

82
00:06:39,692 --> 00:06:43,292
I'll teach my sister-in-law how we do things.

83
00:06:43,292 --> 00:06:45,392
Don't worry, okay?

84
00:06:46,692 --> 00:06:49,031
My husband handpicked

85
00:06:49,031 --> 00:06:52,332
Soonyang Hotel's best cooks and waiting staff.

86
00:06:52,332 --> 00:06:55,372
Don't worry about anything and stay by Father's side.

87
00:06:55,372 --> 00:06:57,112
You're the guest of honor.

88
00:06:57,112 --> 00:07:01,141
It's your father-in-law's birthday, and he's the one who won the medal.

89
00:07:01,141 --> 00:07:02,582
How am I the guest of honor?

90
00:07:02,582 --> 00:07:04,452
Don't say that.

91
00:07:06,211 --> 00:07:09,251
Soonyang owes its immense growth to you, Mother.

92
00:07:09,251 --> 00:07:12,322
Who doesn't know that?

93
00:07:12,322 --> 00:07:15,522
That's such a sweet way of telling me to stop nagging

94
00:07:15,522 --> 00:07:17,991
and get out of the kitchen.

95
00:07:19,461 --> 00:07:21,631
Hello, Hae In.

96
00:07:24,072 --> 00:07:28,202
What should I do, Mother?

97
00:07:28,202 --> 00:07:30,842
Don't even think of doing anything.

98
00:07:30,842 --> 00:07:34,372
Stay with Yoon Ki and the boys.

99
00:07:36,612 --> 00:07:38,852
- Mother, leave it to us. 
 - Okay.

100
00:07:38,852 --> 00:07:41,081
Go on.

101
00:07:42,022 --> 00:07:43,692
Do you want me

102
00:07:43,692 --> 00:07:45,792
- to prepare the fruit? 
 - Mr. Ko, get the fruit.

103
00:07:45,792 --> 00:07:48,091
Yes, Ma'am.

104
00:07:48,091 --> 00:07:49,961
They're gutsy.

105
00:07:49,961 --> 00:07:53,032
He cut off contact to marry a woman his parents disapproved of.

106
00:07:53,032 --> 00:07:55,231
They then show up after ten years

107
00:07:55,231 --> 00:07:58,301
to laugh and smile and enjoy having a family.

108
00:07:59,101 --> 00:08:01,771
I'm incapable of putting on such an act.

109
00:08:01,771 --> 00:08:04,812
She's not like us at all.

110
00:08:04,812 --> 00:08:07,111
She was an actress.

111
00:08:07,111 --> 00:08:09,411
She doesn't suit this family.

112
00:08:09,411 --> 00:08:12,211
She belongs on stage.

113
00:08:12,211 --> 00:08:13,782
Right?

114
00:08:16,452 --> 00:08:19,292
Are you being bullies now because you weren't in school?

115
00:08:19,292 --> 00:08:23,562
You have way too many wrinkles around your eyes.

116
00:08:23,562 --> 00:08:26,792
- Agassi. 
 - What are you doing?

117
00:08:26,792 --> 00:08:30,031
With so many people watching?

118
00:08:30,772 --> 00:08:32,671
Ms. Lee.

119
00:08:35,001 --> 00:08:37,772
Don't try to play a daughter-in-law

120
00:08:37,772 --> 00:08:39,511
and stick to what you have been doing.

121
00:08:39,511 --> 00:08:43,411
Stand still like a portrait and smile prettily.

122
00:08:44,412 --> 00:08:46,311
You're good at that.

123
00:09:01,361 --> 00:09:03,631
 Happy birthday, Sir. 

124
00:09:04,302 --> 00:09:06,471
 Happy birthday, sir. 

125
00:09:06,471 --> 00:09:08,172
 Let's have a drink. 

126
00:09:08,172 --> 00:09:11,542
 - Happy birthday. 
 - Happy birthday, Hyungnim. 

127
00:09:15,942 --> 00:09:18,052
He studied in Tokyo

128
00:09:18,052 --> 00:09:21,981
and works as a master at a sushi restaurant in Ginza.

129
00:09:21,981 --> 00:09:24,892
The Japanese refused to let him go,

130
00:09:24,892 --> 00:09:27,121
but I literally abducted him and got him

131
00:09:27,121 --> 00:09:31,432
on an early flight so he could cater for you today.

132
00:09:31,432 --> 00:09:32,991
It's good, isn't it?

133
00:09:32,991 --> 00:09:34,362
Yes.

134
00:09:34,362 --> 00:09:35,531
I knew it.

135
00:09:35,531 --> 00:09:40,001
Domestic goods still can't compare to Japanese.

136
00:09:42,841 --> 00:09:44,571
How many?

137
00:09:45,511 --> 00:09:48,481
Grains of rice. How many are there?

138
00:09:48,481 --> 00:09:51,682
The ideal weight of fish and rice is 15g...

139
00:09:51,682 --> 00:09:53,511
So how many?

140
00:09:54,351 --> 00:09:58,051
- I apologize, Sir. 
 - There are 320.

141
00:09:58,051 --> 00:10:00,952
A trained sushi master

142
00:10:00,952 --> 00:10:05,131
usually picks up 320 grains of rice to make one piece.

143
00:10:05,131 --> 00:10:08,731
That many might be appropriate for lunch,

144
00:10:08,731 --> 00:10:12,971
but on a day like this, or when served with alcohol,

145
00:10:12,971 --> 00:10:16,201
use just 280 grains of rice, okay?

146
00:10:17,042 --> 00:10:18,842
So it's not too filling.

147
00:10:18,842 --> 00:10:21,111
I'll do that, Chairman.

148
00:10:25,511 --> 00:10:28,351
Cheongwadae sent a messenger, Chairman.

149
00:10:31,091 --> 00:10:34,052
- The Blue House? 
 - Yes.

150
00:10:47,342 --> 00:10:48,602
Chairman.

151
00:10:48,602 --> 00:10:50,341
 Happy birthday. 

152
00:10:50,341 --> 00:10:52,312
Thank you. Eat your fill.

153
00:10:52,312 --> 00:10:54,562
 Thank you. 

154
00:10:56,981 --> 00:11:01,582
Father, how did you know the number of rice grains?

155
00:11:01,582 --> 00:11:05,022
Is there a Japanese restaurant in Soonyang Hotel, yes or no?

156
00:11:05,022 --> 00:11:06,221
Of course...

157
00:11:06,221 --> 00:11:09,422
There. Must I say more?

158
00:11:12,662 --> 00:11:16,161
Hey, you. Deputy CEO of Soonyang Electronics.

159
00:11:16,161 --> 00:11:20,931
Tell me. What are this year's sales?

160
00:11:20,931 --> 00:11:22,602
It's 2.3 billion dollars.

161
00:11:22,602 --> 00:11:24,741
- Up by 15 percent... 
 - And the Japanese?

162
00:11:24,741 --> 00:11:28,641
H made 26.5 billion dollars, and T made 20 billion dollars.

163
00:11:28,641 --> 00:11:30,312
Both made more than ten times we did.

164
00:11:30,312 --> 00:11:33,482
Our deputy CEO is right then.

165
00:11:33,482 --> 00:11:36,621
We still can't compare to the Japanese.

166
00:11:37,892 --> 00:11:39,122
Is that true?

167
00:11:39,122 --> 00:11:41,322
Still, we're number one in our country.

168
00:11:41,322 --> 00:11:43,022
We have never lost

169
00:11:43,022 --> 00:11:45,792
the top spot in Korea in the white goods market.

170
00:11:45,792 --> 00:11:49,401
The top spot… in Korea.

171
00:11:49,401 --> 00:11:51,932
"The top spot in Korea"?

172
00:11:51,932 --> 00:11:54,901
Are you competing in a national competition?

173
00:12:00,682 --> 00:12:02,341
Father.

174
00:12:03,481 --> 00:12:06,352
Yoon Ki wishes to say hello.

175
00:12:09,551 --> 00:12:13,951
Congratulations on winning a medal and happy birthday, Father.

176
00:12:13,951 --> 00:12:17,792
He opened a film distribution company.

177
00:12:17,792 --> 00:12:20,731
His first movie will be shown this year.

178
00:12:20,731 --> 00:12:22,601
Aren't you proud of him?

179
00:12:22,601 --> 00:12:25,572
He did it all without your help.

180
00:12:25,572 --> 00:12:29,341
He will do well. He's your son.

181
00:12:29,341 --> 00:12:34,172
He said he will visit every weekend like the others.

182
00:12:34,172 --> 00:12:36,012
If you permit it.

183
00:12:36,012 --> 00:12:40,511
He did a great job raising both boys.

184
00:12:40,511 --> 00:12:44,581
Hyeong Jun, Do Jun, come and meet your grandfather.

185
00:12:45,591 --> 00:12:47,221
Bow.

186
00:12:47,221 --> 00:12:48,922
Yes, Father.

187
00:12:48,922 --> 00:12:50,662
Don't be so angry with him.

188
00:12:50,662 --> 00:12:53,162
Do movies make money, Mister?

189
00:12:53,861 --> 00:12:55,562
Something more valuable than money...

190
00:12:55,562 --> 00:12:57,701
Will it help Soonyang?

191
00:12:57,701 --> 00:12:59,472
- Father. 
 - It makes no money

192
00:12:59,472 --> 00:13:02,242
and won't help Soonyang.

193
00:13:02,242 --> 00:13:04,741
Why are you my son?

194
00:13:06,741 --> 00:13:09,912
- Chairman. 
 - The guests are leaving.

195
00:13:10,611 --> 00:13:12,611
Throw salt after them.

196
00:13:17,522 --> 00:13:19,322
It really is a party.

197
00:13:19,322 --> 00:13:22,461
There are beggars everywhere.

198
00:13:25,432 --> 00:13:29,062
He doesn't mean what he says.

199
00:13:32,932 --> 00:13:36,402
Yoon Ki, you know what your father's like.

200
00:13:36,402 --> 00:13:39,841
Don't take it to heart, okay?

201
00:13:39,841 --> 00:13:42,042
Yes. Leave it at that today.

202
00:13:42,042 --> 00:13:44,411
Let's take it slowly.

203
00:13:44,411 --> 00:13:45,411
Let's go and eat.

204
00:13:45,411 --> 00:13:48,081
You eat lots.

205
00:13:50,151 --> 00:13:52,452
 He married against his parents' will, 

206
00:13:52,452 --> 00:13:55,292
 so 4-0's succession rights were revoked. 

207
00:13:55,292 --> 00:13:57,022
Hello.

208
00:13:57,022 --> 00:14:00,761
 It’s exactly the same as what I know. 

209
00:14:19,281 --> 00:14:20,852
 But... 

210
00:14:26,022 --> 00:14:27,921
 I'm missing. 

211
00:14:29,522 --> 00:14:33,131
 I know all there is to know about Soonyang's Jin family, 

212
00:14:33,131 --> 00:14:34,501
 but... 

213
00:14:34,501 --> 00:14:36,731
   

214
00:14:36,731 --> 00:14:39,201
   

215
00:14:42,472 --> 00:14:47,042
 I have no information on 4-2 Jin Do Jun. 

216
00:14:48,182 --> 00:14:49,682
 Why... 

217
00:14:49,682 --> 00:14:54,612
 is my mind blank when it comes to 4-2 Jin Do Jun? 

218
00:14:56,081 --> 00:14:57,681
 Why is that? 

219
00:15:04,432 --> 00:15:06,331
You know, Chairman,

220
00:15:06,331 --> 00:15:09,331
how the great 6.29 Declaration came to be.

221
00:15:09,331 --> 00:15:15,741
It was all thanks to the president's concern and thoughtfulness.

222
00:15:15,741 --> 00:15:17,472
History will record him

223
00:15:17,472 --> 00:15:21,572
as the father of democracy in our land.

224
00:15:23,842 --> 00:15:26,411
Try the tea.

225
00:15:26,481 --> 00:15:28,552
It smells lovely.

226
00:15:32,721 --> 00:15:34,771
During the next administration,

227
00:15:35,522 --> 00:15:39,591
shouldn't the average man take the lead role?

228
00:15:40,662 --> 00:15:45,662
History is marching on, and Soonyang should join the flow.

229
00:15:47,131 --> 00:15:51,472
The president wishes to give you an opportunity.

230
00:15:59,182 --> 00:16:00,951
Mr. Lee.

231
00:16:00,951 --> 00:16:02,352
Yes, Sir.

232
00:16:03,922 --> 00:16:06,221
Were you aware?

233
00:16:06,952 --> 00:16:11,731
This gentleman from the Blue House knew.

234
00:16:18,171 --> 00:16:21,841
This medal you see here.

235
00:16:22,801 --> 00:16:24,901
This is a deferred payment.

236
00:16:26,641 --> 00:16:29,282
He came here to collect.

237
00:16:31,811 --> 00:16:33,511
So

238
00:16:36,521 --> 00:16:39,751
how much do you want for it?

239
00:16:54,071 --> 00:16:58,942
♪   Your window just won't open   ♪

240
00:16:59,811 --> 00:17:04,211
♪   I'll knock on it with the moonlight of love   ♪

241
00:17:20,491 --> 00:17:25,372
♪   Oh, my love   ♪

242
00:17:25,372 --> 00:17:29,442
♪   Open the window to let in the breeze   ♪

243
00:17:50,262 --> 00:17:52,732
Vice-Chairman Jin Seong Jun?

244
00:18:00,102 --> 00:18:02,741
It's obvious what movies make money.

245
00:18:02,741 --> 00:18:04,872
- Hong Kongers shooting guns. 
 - "A Better Tomorrow"?

246
00:18:04,872 --> 00:18:07,712
- Or Americans going to war. 
 - "Platoon."

247
00:18:07,712 --> 00:18:09,841
So what kind of movie are you making?

248
00:18:09,841 --> 00:18:12,611
It's about the French people praying.

249
00:18:12,611 --> 00:18:14,721
It's called "Under the Sun of Satan."

250
00:18:14,721 --> 00:18:18,151
I thought you wanted to make a movie, not build a hotel.

251
00:18:18,151 --> 00:18:21,442
Do you want to make everyone fall asleep?

252
00:18:21,442 --> 00:18:24,362
Dad! Do Jun is in trouble.

253
00:18:24,362 --> 00:18:26,092
He's upstairs now.

254
00:18:36,272 --> 00:18:40,341
You broke this vase. Okay, boy?

255
00:18:40,341 --> 00:18:42,812
We're the only ones in this room right now.

256
00:18:42,812 --> 00:18:47,411
No matter what you say, everyone will believe me.

257
00:18:48,122 --> 00:18:51,252
Why? Because I'm the rightful heir to the throne,

258
00:18:51,252 --> 00:18:54,102
and Grandpa will side with me no matter what.

259
00:19:05,771 --> 00:19:07,072
Did you just scoff?

260
00:19:07,072 --> 00:19:10,472
You were a real mess even when you were young.

261
00:19:10,472 --> 00:19:13,071
What? Have you lost your mind?

262
00:19:13,071 --> 00:19:15,211
Seong Jun!

263
00:19:18,052 --> 00:19:21,251
- Hey. My gosh, are you all right? 
 - What happened?

264
00:19:21,251 --> 00:19:23,281
- Do you know how much this costs? 
 - Are you okay?

265
00:19:23,281 --> 00:19:26,681
Father absolutely treasures this porcelain vase.

266
00:19:26,681 --> 00:19:28,092
It was him.

267
00:19:28,092 --> 00:19:31,792
He broke it. He tried to run away, but I caught him.

268
00:19:31,792 --> 00:19:34,731
- Oh, dear. 
 - Do Jun.

269
00:19:34,731 --> 00:19:37,602
Is that true?

270
00:19:39,471 --> 00:19:42,302
Hold on. Yoon Ki.

271
00:19:42,302 --> 00:19:44,202
This is making me very uncomfortable.

272
00:19:44,202 --> 00:19:48,682
Are you implying that Seong Jun could be lying?

273
00:19:48,682 --> 00:19:50,641
How could you accuse Seong Jun of lying...

274
00:19:50,641 --> 00:19:53,652
He is lying.

275
00:19:53,652 --> 00:19:56,452
What? What do you mean?

276
00:19:56,452 --> 00:19:58,521
The vase...

277
00:20:01,692 --> 00:20:03,961
He's the one who broke it.

278
00:20:05,862 --> 00:20:08,762
He was trying to steal the chairman's belonging.

279
00:20:08,762 --> 00:20:11,261
I caught him in the act.

280
00:20:27,051 --> 00:20:29,852
He got flustered and tried to run away, but...

281
00:20:29,852 --> 00:20:31,321
- Hey! 
 - No!

282
00:20:31,321 --> 00:20:33,452
- Seong Jun! 
 - Do Jun.

283
00:20:33,452 --> 00:20:35,320
- Are you all right? 
 - What is going on?

284
00:20:36,252 --> 00:20:39,691
- Father. 
 - Seong Jun...

285
00:20:39,691 --> 00:20:41,332
It wasn't me, Grandpa.

286
00:20:41,332 --> 00:20:44,702
- I didn't break it. I swear... 
 - Enough.

287
00:20:45,931 --> 00:20:48,372
Shut your mouth.

288
00:20:53,512 --> 00:20:55,712
 This happened in 1987, 

289
00:20:55,712 --> 00:20:58,112
 at the sixtieth birthday party for your grandfather, 

290
00:20:58,112 --> 00:21:00,652
 former Chairman Jin. 

291
00:21:00,652 --> 00:21:03,482
 1987. 

292
00:21:03,482 --> 00:21:06,092
 Chairman Jin Yang Cheol. 

293
00:21:08,422 --> 00:21:13,561
 And his sixtieth birthday party, you smashed the Goryeo celadon that he cherished 

294
00:21:13,561 --> 00:21:17,461
 and were scolded by him for the first time. 

295
00:21:17,461 --> 00:21:19,672
 The smashed vase? 

296
00:21:20,801 --> 00:21:23,102
Seong Jun.

297
00:21:23,102 --> 00:21:25,972
Do you know what you did wrong?

298
00:21:28,182 --> 00:21:29,811
Come here.

299
00:21:32,352 --> 00:21:34,052
Sit down.

300
00:21:40,622 --> 00:21:45,621
You see, I don't care about this vase.

301
00:21:45,621 --> 00:21:49,731
Seong Jun, you will continue my legacy

302
00:21:49,731 --> 00:21:53,632
and become the owner of Soonyang in the future.

303
00:21:53,632 --> 00:21:55,242
Okay?

304
00:21:56,772 --> 00:21:59,812
Everything you say

305
00:21:59,812 --> 00:22:02,712
and do

306
00:22:02,712 --> 00:22:05,642
could make or break ten thousand employees' livelihoods.

307
00:22:06,582 --> 00:22:10,722
Even their families' livelihoods will depend on you.

308
00:22:15,021 --> 00:22:19,031
Yet you can't even keep your emotions under control?

309
00:22:19,031 --> 00:22:21,492
Acting up like this

310
00:22:24,432 --> 00:22:26,401
 It wasn't an adequate quality... 

311
00:22:26,401 --> 00:22:28,602
"Isn't an adequate quality..."

312
00:22:28,602 --> 00:22:30,502
isn't an adequate quality...

313
00:22:30,502 --> 00:22:34,511
"in someone who will run a business that is Soonyang."

314
00:22:34,511 --> 00:22:38,652
in someone who will run the business

315
00:22:38,652 --> 00:22:41,311
that is Soonyang.

316
00:22:43,352 --> 00:22:46,221
 What I read in his autobiography is unfolding before my eyes. 

317
00:22:46,221 --> 00:22:48,921
 It was white porcelain. 

318
00:22:50,162 --> 00:22:53,561
 My grandfather's vase that I broke. 

319
00:22:53,561 --> 00:22:57,032
 It wasn't Goryeo celadon. It was a white porcelain vase. 

320
00:23:03,901 --> 00:23:05,701
 Everything is happening 

321
00:23:05,701 --> 00:23:10,182
 exactly as I know it. 

322
00:23:23,122 --> 00:23:25,931
 The past as I know it. 

323
00:23:25,931 --> 00:23:29,761
 I'm in Korea in the year 1987. 

324
00:23:31,701 --> 00:23:33,410
 Then... 

325
00:23:33,410 --> 00:23:34,800
   

326
00:23:34,801 --> 00:23:36,101
 If that's the case... 

327
00:23:36,101 --> 00:23:38,380
   

328
00:23:38,380 --> 00:23:41,780
   

329
00:23:52,291 --> 00:23:54,422
   

330
00:24:01,401 --> 00:24:04,101
That was a great meal. Let's go.

331
00:24:09,471 --> 00:24:11,572
- Thank you. 
 - Did you enjoy the food?

332
00:24:11,572 --> 00:24:14,271
- Yes. 
 - Go back safely.

333
00:24:14,271 --> 00:24:16,042
Hyeon Min?

334
00:24:38,132 --> 00:24:40,102
Mom.

335
00:24:49,682 --> 00:24:52,112
   

336
00:24:52,112 --> 00:24:54,351
- Hyeon Min! 
 - You're here.

337
00:24:54,351 --> 00:24:55,781
Dad!

338
00:24:55,781 --> 00:24:57,152
Hi, Hyeon Min!

339
00:24:57,152 --> 00:25:00,392
Lucky you, Hyeon Min! Daddy picked up fried chicken for you.

340
00:25:00,392 --> 00:25:02,392
Who do you like more? Mommy or Daddy?

341
00:25:02,392 --> 00:25:04,661
Mommy!

342
00:25:04,661 --> 00:25:06,162
- I knew it! 
 - I'll do better.

343
00:25:06,162 --> 00:25:07,832
- Do you need a hand? 
 - No, I'm good.

344
00:25:07,832 --> 00:25:10,782
Come on. Let's have this fried chicken.

345
00:25:17,771 --> 00:25:20,842
 We found Do Jun. 

346
00:25:20,842 --> 00:25:23,641
We'll get there soon, too.

347
00:25:23,641 --> 00:25:26,182
Thank you, Section Chief Oh.

348
00:25:26,182 --> 00:25:27,911
Okay.

349
00:25:29,222 --> 00:25:32,372
Do Jun is okay. You can put your worries to rest now.

350
00:25:33,892 --> 00:25:35,861
Thank goodness.

351
00:25:38,532 --> 00:25:40,461
Hello...

352
00:25:44,832 --> 00:25:46,430
Are you here alone?

353
00:25:46,430 --> 00:25:49,000
Are your parents not here with you?

354
00:25:51,872 --> 00:25:55,941
Can I have one serving of gukbap (rice soup)?

355
00:25:57,612 --> 00:26:01,482
Sure. You can take that table over there.

356
00:27:00,112 --> 00:27:01,911
Hello...

357
00:27:01,911 --> 00:27:03,741
Do Jun.

358
00:27:08,882 --> 00:27:13,052
What are you doing here? I was so worried.

359
00:27:15,221 --> 00:27:18,521
Get up. Let's go.

360
00:27:18,521 --> 00:27:20,992
Let's go home.

361
00:27:22,332 --> 00:27:27,102
Let's talk at home.

362
00:27:53,192 --> 00:27:57,031
   

363
00:28:05,672 --> 00:28:07,641
What's wrong, Do Jun?

364
00:28:07,641 --> 00:28:09,742
What is it?

365
00:28:12,251 --> 00:28:14,451
I'm relieved.

366
00:28:16,922 --> 00:28:19,592
Mom's alive.

367
00:28:20,952 --> 00:28:23,792
I'm so relieved.

368
00:28:29,761 --> 00:28:31,931
Mom is relieved, too.

369
00:28:32,702 --> 00:28:35,402
Thank goodness.

370
00:28:36,842 --> 00:28:39,511
I have you.

371
00:28:41,112 --> 00:28:42,881
Don't cry.

372
00:28:55,592 --> 00:28:59,592
That poor thing must've been so scared. Look how he ran away.

373
00:29:01,561 --> 00:29:03,602
Well done.

374
00:29:04,261 --> 00:29:08,502
Way to go.

375
00:29:09,902 --> 00:29:14,041
Your son and grandsons came to see you after ten years.

376
00:29:14,041 --> 00:29:17,112
How could you read a book after kicking them out like that?

377
00:29:17,112 --> 00:29:20,211
My son and grandsons? Whom?

378
00:29:20,211 --> 00:29:23,182
I only scolded my eldest grandson,

379
00:29:23,182 --> 00:29:24,982
Seong Jun. No one else.

380
00:29:24,982 --> 00:29:28,092
You can't expect all your children to be the same.

381
00:29:28,092 --> 00:29:31,321
Let at least one of them do what they want.

382
00:29:31,321 --> 00:29:35,062
I fed them and paid for their education, so I must get my money's worth.

383
00:29:35,062 --> 00:29:38,132
I never invest in things where I can't get my money's worth.

384
00:29:39,632 --> 00:29:43,141
You'd better not coddle Yoon Ki.

385
00:29:46,442 --> 00:29:48,342
The others will turn out like him.

386
00:30:07,592 --> 00:30:11,832
 The only person in this family who I know nothing about 

387
00:30:11,832 --> 00:30:15,742
 is me, 4-2 Jin Do Jun. 

388
00:30:16,541 --> 00:30:20,471
 Am I living as Jin Do Jun now because I'm possessed? 

389
00:30:20,471 --> 00:30:22,311
   

390
00:30:28,452 --> 00:30:29,952
   

391
00:30:29,952 --> 00:30:33,521
- Mom. 
 - Hi, Son!

392
00:30:33,521 --> 00:30:34,592
Hey, you. Come here.

393
00:30:34,592 --> 00:30:37,261
- Oh, look at you. 
 - Gosh, stop!

394
00:30:37,261 --> 00:30:40,162
- Run! Go! 
 - Hey, where are you going?

395
00:30:40,162 --> 00:30:44,201
- Oh, nice one. 
 - Let's cheer for your brother!

396
00:30:44,201 --> 00:30:47,731
- Nice. 
 - Well done.

397
00:30:48,801 --> 00:30:51,001
 Or did I simply travel back in time? 

398
00:30:51,001 --> 00:30:54,111
 If not that... Have I been reincarnated? 

399
00:30:54,111 --> 00:30:56,481
 How did this happen? 

400
00:30:56,481 --> 00:30:58,282
   

401
00:31:03,582 --> 00:31:05,682
Why are you still up?

402
00:31:05,682 --> 00:31:07,521
It's getting late.

403
00:31:10,362 --> 00:31:14,731
Do Jun, what happened today... It must've been a lot for you.

404
00:31:27,041 --> 00:31:31,642
At first, I felt the same way.

405
00:31:32,481 --> 00:31:34,981
"What am I doing here?"

406
00:31:34,981 --> 00:31:38,622
"I don't belong in this world."

407
00:31:38,622 --> 00:31:42,821
I couldn't understand them. It was very frustrating.

408
00:31:43,422 --> 00:31:46,431
Did you feel the same way?

409
00:31:47,862 --> 00:31:48,832
Does that mean...

410
00:31:48,832 --> 00:31:50,740
It felt so foreign to me.

411
00:31:50,740 --> 00:31:54,670
I was scared, and it was uncomfortable.

412
00:31:54,670 --> 00:31:59,072
I almost regretted marrying your dad.

413
00:32:01,241 --> 00:32:04,712
But now, it's not so bad.

414
00:32:06,611 --> 00:32:12,792
I found a reason to accept them as my family.

415
00:32:13,452 --> 00:32:15,521
A reason to accept them as your family?

416
00:32:15,521 --> 00:32:19,161
You and Hyeong Jun.

417
00:32:19,892 --> 00:32:26,332
Do Jun, I'm certain that you'll find your reason too, one day.

418
00:32:45,592 --> 00:32:49,192
All the companies are dropping their prices for their 64K DRAMs.

419
00:32:49,922 --> 00:32:53,272
Soonyang Semiconductor started exporting them this month.

420
00:32:53,272 --> 00:32:55,461
Japan and the US are already dominating the market.

421
00:32:55,461 --> 00:32:58,231
So if they're charging less than half of what we're asking for,

422
00:32:58,231 --> 00:33:01,881
Soonyang Semiconductor will not survive in the market, Chairman.

423
00:33:04,442 --> 00:33:08,642
What time is it now... in New York?

424
00:33:09,811 --> 00:33:11,142
It's 9 p.m., Sir.

425
00:33:11,142 --> 00:33:13,251
Is Im Pil Sung in New York now?

426
00:33:13,251 --> 00:33:15,122
I'll tell him to give you a call at once.

427
00:33:15,122 --> 00:33:17,322
No, don't wake him up.

428
00:33:18,252 --> 00:33:20,921
Just tell him to fax it over when he wakes up.

429
00:33:20,921 --> 00:33:23,522
- Fax? What do you need, Sir? 
 - His resignation letter.

430
00:33:23,522 --> 00:33:25,191
Pardon me?

431
00:33:30,962 --> 00:33:36,971
I didn't know that a knife was being held to my throat... until I read that newspaper.

432
00:33:39,372 --> 00:33:41,522
Do you think that this is acceptable?

433
00:33:43,682 --> 00:33:46,451
Did he go to the US to eat hamburgers?

434
00:33:47,111 --> 00:33:49,761
I'm done paying for his hamburgers.

435
00:33:51,682 --> 00:33:52,892
I saw the news, Father.

436
00:33:52,892 --> 00:33:57,122
The American companies slashed their price from 3 to 1.80 dollars.

437
00:33:57,122 --> 00:34:00,591
And the Japanese companies said they would sell it for 0.30 dollars.

438
00:34:00,591 --> 00:34:03,202
If we sell ours at the price the Japanese companies are offering,

439
00:34:03,202 --> 00:34:07,132
we will lose 130 million dollars this year alone.

440
00:34:07,132 --> 00:34:10,632
We're like shrimp... getting squashed between two fighting whales.

441
00:34:10,632 --> 00:34:12,521
The semiconductor business...

442
00:34:13,142 --> 00:34:14,942
Let's just give up here.

443
00:34:14,942 --> 00:34:16,781
I'm afraid we came too far.

444
00:34:16,781 --> 00:34:20,441
- The initial investment alone... 
 - Right, so let's cut our losses and call it quits.

445
00:34:21,182 --> 00:34:24,032
Let's stop trying to fill a bottomless pit.

446
00:34:24,032 --> 00:34:26,682
Youngjin Semiconductor has given up too.

447
00:34:26,682 --> 00:34:29,402
They're being sold to a Japanese company.

448
00:34:30,562 --> 00:34:34,332
Think of the question you always ask us.

449
00:34:34,332 --> 00:34:36,982
Will the semiconductor business bring in money?

450
00:34:39,372 --> 00:34:42,042
   

451
00:34:46,911 --> 00:34:49,812
What brings you by at this hour?

452
00:34:49,812 --> 00:34:53,681
I'm sorry for causing you concern yesterday.

453
00:34:58,182 --> 00:35:00,721
I'm here to apologize to Grandpa.

454
00:35:01,352 --> 00:35:06,191
Look at you talking like a grown man. You're so mature.

455
00:35:06,191 --> 00:35:09,332
Come with me. He's upstairs in his study.

456
00:35:09,332 --> 00:35:10,901
Come on.

457
00:35:17,002 --> 00:35:19,542
Children should behave like Children.

458
00:35:19,542 --> 00:35:23,682
Is she naive? Or is she becoming dense?

459
00:35:23,682 --> 00:35:26,182
- Hey. 
 - I'm talking about Mother.

460
00:35:26,182 --> 00:35:28,082
Oh.

461
00:35:28,082 --> 00:35:29,551
Isn't it so obvious?

462
00:35:29,551 --> 00:35:32,551
Clearly, he memorized what his father told him to say.

463
00:35:32,551 --> 00:35:34,901
He's talking like a man in his forties.

464
00:35:37,122 --> 00:35:38,892
Wait here.

465
00:35:38,892 --> 00:35:41,832
He'll be out soon.

466
00:35:41,832 --> 00:35:43,761
You can watch TV if you get bored.

467
00:35:43,761 --> 00:35:45,561
- Okay. 
 - All right, then.

468
00:35:50,471 --> 00:35:52,042
   

469
00:35:52,042 --> 00:35:54,992
   

470
00:36:02,051 --> 00:36:04,122
You should deliver the campaign fund yourself

471
00:36:04,122 --> 00:36:06,852
and meet him in person.

472
00:36:06,852 --> 00:36:08,252
What?

473
00:36:08,962 --> 00:36:11,921
The general election will take place in April next year.

474
00:36:11,921 --> 00:36:13,891
You need a nomination.

475
00:36:14,832 --> 00:36:18,261
Oh, right. Honey, you know everything.

476
00:36:18,261 --> 00:36:20,702
You sure take after Father.

477
00:36:25,841 --> 00:36:28,341
I heard you had visitors from Cheongwadae yesterday.

478
00:36:28,341 --> 00:36:31,341
Did they ask you to back Roh Tae Woo's campaign?

479
00:36:34,212 --> 00:36:38,682
Director Lee only listens and never spills what he hears.

480
00:36:38,682 --> 00:36:41,652
I'm your daughter, Father. Of course, I know that much.

481
00:36:41,652 --> 00:36:43,591
You silly goose.

482
00:36:43,591 --> 00:36:45,721
Take a seat.

483
00:36:45,721 --> 00:36:47,562
You too.

484
00:36:49,062 --> 00:36:53,502
Instead of calling you to Cheongwadae, they came all the way here.

485
00:36:53,502 --> 00:36:55,501
It means the tables have turned.

486
00:36:55,501 --> 00:36:57,672
It tells me that Roh Tae Woo is at a disadvantage.

487
00:36:57,672 --> 00:37:02,541
I'm not surprised. After all the protests and uprisings... to end the military dictatorship,

488
00:37:02,541 --> 00:37:05,152
who'd want to vote for another Military Academy graduate?

489
00:37:05,152 --> 00:37:08,151
Unless the entire nation is suffering from amnesia collectively.

490
00:37:08,151 --> 00:37:10,152
The two Kims will agree on a single candidacy soon.

491
00:37:10,152 --> 00:37:12,452
The opposition power will win this time, Father.

492
00:37:12,452 --> 00:37:14,221
That being said,

493
00:37:14,221 --> 00:37:17,522
shouldn't you decide which candidate to support now?

494
00:37:17,522 --> 00:37:19,591
Between DJ and YS, choose the one who's more likely to win...

495
00:37:19,591 --> 00:37:23,361
Right. So who would that be?

496
00:37:23,361 --> 00:37:25,102
DJ, obviously.

497
00:37:25,102 --> 00:37:30,002
He is supported by all the student and civic groups... that helped establish the direct election system.

498
00:37:31,471 --> 00:37:34,042
Dong Ki, you should never get into politics.

499
00:37:34,042 --> 00:37:36,779
We should support YS, not DJ.

500
00:37:36,779 --> 00:37:38,781
I know DJ has many fans, but he also has many enemies.

501
00:37:38,781 --> 00:37:42,181
When it's a neck-and-neck fight, the one with less enemies will win.

502
00:37:43,182 --> 00:37:46,182
Aren't you saying that because you dislike DJ?

503
00:37:46,182 --> 00:37:51,452
I heard Kim Dae Jung was against... nominating Chang Je since he worked as a public security prosecutor.

504
00:37:52,332 --> 00:37:54,361
Why are you roping Chang Je into this?

505
00:37:54,361 --> 00:37:57,461
I am saying these things for the sake of the company's future.

506
00:37:58,202 --> 00:38:01,401
- Father! 
 - Be quiet.

507
00:38:01,401 --> 00:38:04,671
I'm sorry for causing you concern, Father.

508
00:38:04,671 --> 00:38:06,471
- Mr. Lee. 
 - Yes, Sir.

509
00:38:06,471 --> 00:38:08,571
As for their approval ratings,

510
00:38:08,571 --> 00:38:11,912
get Soonyang Economic Research Institute to look into it.

511
00:38:11,912 --> 00:38:15,082
Tell them to find out which one of them deserves my money more.

512
00:38:15,082 --> 00:38:16,822
Yes, Sir.

513
00:38:18,252 --> 00:38:20,451
Now, get out.

514
00:38:23,162 --> 00:38:26,291
- Oh. 
 - Hey, aren't you Yoon Ki's son?

515
00:38:26,291 --> 00:38:30,762
I'm here to apologize to Grandpa for what happened yesterday.

516
00:38:30,762 --> 00:38:35,402
Oh, my. Yoon Ki always had a sly side to him.

517
00:38:35,402 --> 00:38:40,402
After not visiting us once for ten years, he sends his son here daily.

518
00:38:40,402 --> 00:38:43,582
Did he come all the way here by himself because his parents told him to?

519
00:38:43,582 --> 00:38:45,582
He sure takes after his father.

520
00:38:45,582 --> 00:38:49,012
Good-looking and calculating.

521
00:38:50,051 --> 00:38:53,192
Your youngest son's child is here to see you, Sir.

522
00:38:53,192 --> 00:38:56,592
I only have two sons. I didn't know I had another son!

523
00:38:56,592 --> 00:38:59,592
 I will talk to him and send him home, Sir. 

524
00:39:02,132 --> 00:39:04,932
Come with us. Let's go downstairs.

525
00:39:05,772 --> 00:39:08,702
Please tell Grandpa...

526
00:39:08,702 --> 00:39:13,871
that I'm here to pay for the vase that was broken yesterday.

527
00:39:13,871 --> 00:39:14,911
That punk.

528
00:39:14,911 --> 00:39:17,411
Hey! You little brat.

529
00:39:17,411 --> 00:39:21,882
Hey, do you even know how much that vase costs?

530
00:39:21,882 --> 00:39:23,752
Five bills?

