00:39:23,752 --> 00:39:26,491
It can't cost more than that.

532
00:39:26,491 --> 00:39:29,391
Five bills? What? Five dollars?

533
00:39:29,391 --> 00:39:31,962
Or 50 dollars?

534
00:39:33,761 --> 00:39:35,611
No, five million dollars.

535
00:39:36,861 --> 00:39:39,702
What? Five million?

536
00:39:42,772 --> 00:39:46,922
Wouldn't that be enough to fund a presidential election campaign?

537
00:39:48,882 --> 00:39:51,332
 What? Presidential election campaign? 

538
00:39:52,752 --> 00:39:55,282
Please let Grandpa know.

539
00:39:55,282 --> 00:39:59,892
If it were me, I'd back Roh Tae Woo's campaign.

540
00:40:02,292 --> 00:40:06,361
Roh Tae Woo will become President.

541
00:40:08,361 --> 00:40:12,161
Did you eavesdrop on the adults' conversation?

542
00:40:12,161 --> 00:40:15,102
Clearly, your parents couldn't teach you any better.

543
00:40:15,102 --> 00:40:18,441
Is this how your parents taught you?

544
00:40:18,441 --> 00:40:22,342
No one teaches their children to be so brazen.

545
00:40:22,342 --> 00:40:26,141
Just like how no one tells their children to steal their grandfather's things.

546
00:40:26,141 --> 00:40:28,551
- Do Jun. 
 - What?

547
00:40:30,051 --> 00:40:32,351
Young Ki, you must be getting old.

548
00:40:32,351 --> 00:40:35,591
He's just a kid. Why are you getting so worked up?

549
00:40:35,591 --> 00:40:38,692
He read some newspapers, so he's trying to sound like an adult.

550
00:40:38,692 --> 00:40:42,692
Once DJ and YS agree on a unified candidate, Roh Tae Woo can't win.

551
00:40:42,692 --> 00:40:44,502
I assure you that he won't win.

552
00:40:44,502 --> 00:40:47,032
Unified candidacy?

553
00:40:47,032 --> 00:40:51,031
Do you think the two of them will actually reach an agreement?

554
00:40:57,942 --> 00:41:00,181
I do not think so.

555
00:41:02,621 --> 00:41:05,422
Now, that should be enough to compensate him for the broken vase.

556
00:41:05,422 --> 00:41:09,052
I'll be off then.

557
00:41:09,052 --> 00:41:10,991
Goodness.

558
00:41:12,661 --> 00:41:18,062
Oh, my. Yoon Ki did a great job, bringing up such a smart boy.

559
00:41:18,062 --> 00:41:19,672
Oh, sorry.

560
00:41:19,672 --> 00:41:21,032
Of course, it's nonsense.

561
00:41:21,032 --> 00:41:23,371
So many people are rooting for a single candidacy.

562
00:41:23,371 --> 00:41:25,942
They won't betray the majority opinion.

563
00:41:25,942 --> 00:41:27,911
Both YS and DJ...

564
00:41:27,911 --> 00:41:33,511
have come this far because of their devotion.

565
00:41:33,511 --> 00:41:37,222
They won't gamble on their political careers.

566
00:41:37,222 --> 00:41:39,252
Exactly.

567
00:41:40,991 --> 00:41:45,091
Mr. Oh, take Mr. Chairman's grandson home.

568
00:41:46,632 --> 00:41:50,482
Sir, there's breaking news about the presidential election.

569
00:41:50,482 --> 00:41:52,761
You should see it.

570
00:41:52,761 --> 00:41:54,771
What's the matter?

571
00:41:56,002 --> 00:41:58,201
 Kim Young Sam and Kim Dae Jung of the Democratic Party 

572
00:41:58,201 --> 00:42:02,281
 decided against unified candidacy earlier today. 

573
00:42:02,281 --> 00:42:05,382
 Kim Dae Jung clearly expressed 

574
00:42:05,382 --> 00:42:07,712
 that he was against the party convention, 

575
00:42:07,712 --> 00:42:10,882
 which means they will both run for President. 

576
00:42:10,882 --> 00:42:12,152
Father.

577
00:42:12,152 --> 00:42:14,521
 Kim Young Sam and Kim Dae Jung met again... 

578
00:42:14,521 --> 00:42:17,062
- Father! 
 -  to negotiate the details... 

579
00:42:17,062 --> 00:42:19,161
 regarding unified candidacy but failed to reach an agreement. 

580
00:42:19,161 --> 00:42:22,261
 Their talk ended when they decided 

581
00:42:22,261 --> 00:42:25,102
 to postpone the deadline to next Monday, 

582
00:42:25,102 --> 00:42:28,602
 which is when Kim Dae Jung would have to reply by. 

583
00:42:28,602 --> 00:42:31,341
Wait, stop!

584
00:42:36,741 --> 00:42:39,341
Chairman would like to speak with you.

585
00:42:39,341 --> 00:42:41,482
Right now.

586
00:42:44,482 --> 00:42:46,551
Tell me.

587
00:42:47,352 --> 00:42:50,061
How did you know they'd decide against a unified candidacy?

588
00:42:50,061 --> 00:42:53,192
I wouldn't be able to concede. That's why.

589
00:42:53,192 --> 00:42:55,242
Because I'd get greedy.

590
00:42:55,242 --> 00:42:58,431
When three candidates are running for class president,

591
00:42:58,431 --> 00:43:01,281
the top two candidates will never join hands...

592
00:43:01,281 --> 00:43:04,672
because they both believe that they will win.

593
00:43:04,672 --> 00:43:08,612
Rather, they'll do whatever it takes to make each other lose.

594
00:43:08,612 --> 00:43:11,812
They'll bad-mouth each other and fight.

595
00:43:11,812 --> 00:43:15,152
Then their teachers and classmates

596
00:43:15,152 --> 00:43:18,352
will realize that they, in fact, don't deserve the position.

597
00:43:18,352 --> 00:43:21,021
Just like that, they'll drag each other down.

598
00:43:21,021 --> 00:43:25,061
So the one who was least likely to win will end up winning.

599
00:43:25,061 --> 00:43:27,162
Do you mean he'll win by default?

600
00:43:27,162 --> 00:43:30,601
Roh Tae Woo will become President by default.

601
00:43:30,601 --> 00:43:35,371
So I should back Roh Tae Woo. Is that right?

602
00:43:36,641 --> 00:43:40,842
If I were you, I'd give him the money before he became number one.

603
00:43:40,842 --> 00:43:45,481
A lot more than the amount he may be expecting.

604
00:43:45,481 --> 00:43:48,911
He'll be grateful if you give it to him when he's still number three.

605
00:43:48,911 --> 00:43:54,221
But if you wait until he becomes number one, he'll take it for granted.

606
00:44:01,332 --> 00:44:04,531
- Director Lee. 
 - Yes, Chairman.

607
00:44:04,531 --> 00:44:07,771
Tell Manager Oh to have the car ready.

608
00:44:07,771 --> 00:44:09,601
Yes, Sir.

609
00:44:12,641 --> 00:44:16,071
- Hey. 
 - Manager Oh, have the car ready.

610
00:44:16,071 --> 00:44:18,181
Let me ask you one more question then.

