00:44:51,271 --> 00:44:55,051
Then do you think there's a way

621
00:44:55,051 --> 00:44:59,582
for the shrimp to beat the whales?

622
00:45:13,301 --> 00:45:16,301
You're just like other children, after all.

623
00:45:29,281 --> 00:45:31,181
Hey.

624
00:45:31,181 --> 00:45:32,781
Come here.

625
00:45:38,821 --> 00:45:43,991
How did you know the candidacy wouldn't be unified?

626
00:45:43,991 --> 00:45:46,362
Yoon Ki, no.

627
00:45:46,362 --> 00:45:49,432
Did your father tell you so?

628
00:45:52,612 --> 00:45:54,641
My brother said so.

629
00:45:54,641 --> 00:45:56,641
Your brother?

630
00:45:56,641 --> 00:45:59,491
This is what we do in times like these.

631
00:45:59,491 --> 00:46:03,281
"It's obvious at a single glance."

632
00:46:03,281 --> 00:46:04,482
What's with this punk?

633
00:46:04,482 --> 00:46:06,692
That's a buzzword by Hwang Ki Soon.

634
00:46:06,692 --> 00:46:07,951
Hwang Ki...

635
00:46:07,951 --> 00:46:11,351
You punk! That's not the way you should talk to your elders.

636
00:46:12,462 --> 00:46:16,761
Do you think there's a way for a shrimp to win against a whale?

637
00:46:16,761 --> 00:46:20,382
I guess you can't give up on the semiconductors, Chairman.

638
00:46:21,701 --> 00:46:24,751
Why do you think I'm so set on semiconductors?

639
00:46:26,971 --> 00:46:32,212
Last summer, in Mokpo, Ulsan, and Changwon,

640
00:46:32,212 --> 00:46:35,882
when the laborers in our factories put on headbands

641
00:46:35,882 --> 00:46:38,582
and stood there protesting

642
00:46:38,582 --> 00:46:42,152
with cranes and excavators, asking me for a raise

643
00:46:42,152 --> 00:46:44,602
and the formation of a labor union,

644
00:46:45,491 --> 00:46:49,691
I had only one thought

645
00:46:50,862 --> 00:46:54,202
in my head.

646
00:46:56,141 --> 00:47:00,102
I am done doing business by using laborers.

647
00:47:00,102 --> 00:47:01,542
Then...

648
00:47:01,542 --> 00:47:03,942
From now on,

649
00:47:03,942 --> 00:47:07,232
we must do business with technology to make a living.

650
00:47:09,551 --> 00:47:15,351
Semiconductors are the future of Soonyang.

651
00:47:16,521 --> 00:47:17,362
I see.

652
00:47:17,362 --> 00:47:20,112
Do you ask if it'll be worth any money?

653
00:47:23,502 --> 00:47:26,971
Am I the only one who sees this?

654
00:47:28,931 --> 00:47:32,781
Why is there nobody else who can think like this old man?

655
00:47:34,141 --> 00:47:38,812
We have to make an astronomical investment, but we do not know if it'll be a success.

656
00:47:38,812 --> 00:47:42,352
The semiconductor business is nothing but a risk,

657
00:47:42,352 --> 00:47:45,062
no, more like gambling at this point, Chairman.

658
00:47:48,991 --> 00:47:50,261
Once our finances look better

659
00:47:50,261 --> 00:47:53,332
by overseas construction business with the government's cooperation,

660
00:47:53,332 --> 00:47:56,782
why don't you resume the semiconductor business then?

661
00:47:56,782 --> 00:48:00,101
Do you know what democratization is?

662
00:48:00,101 --> 00:48:01,871
I'm not sure.

663
00:48:01,871 --> 00:48:07,111
Before, only a single soldier was after the money in my pocket.

664
00:48:07,111 --> 00:48:12,082
That turned into three civilians.

665
00:48:12,082 --> 00:48:14,381
That's democratization.

666
00:48:32,772 --> 00:48:35,171
   

667
00:48:45,382 --> 00:48:47,982
Please pass this on to the president.

668
00:48:47,982 --> 00:48:54,301
Tell him that I believe he will surely put an end to this era of military dictatorship.

669
00:48:54,301 --> 00:48:56,352
Thank you.

